text: So many people making their own mask these days, if cloth mask so effective why they don’t use in the hospital? So I’ve brought in some anti-microbial mask for toddlers!

answers.text: @phoebepopsicles In other words, due to the shortage of professional masks, medical staffs need them more than us as they are exposed to covid-19 patients the most. Do not hoard professional face masks. We can help ourselves with reusable masks given free by our government or a cloth mask. Change our mindset - the masks we non-medical staff are wearing are aimed to protect others from us, not the other way round.

@phoebepopsicles Need to change the mindset. The cloth mask used by the public is to protect others from you, not to protect you from others. Since everyone is a potential carrier, so if everyone is wearing masks, it helps to reduce transmissions when one starts to talk, laugh, sneeze or cough. It is a win-win situation. The professional mask used by medical staff is to protect them from patients and other ppl.
@lovetreesnfruits Well said, couldn’t agree more! 👏🏻

Oh don’t get me wrong. 😅 I am not saying that the cloth mask won’t protect others from you, and I and not saying that it won’t help reduce transmissions. And of course the priority should be given to medical workers to access these surgical masks and we should definitely not hoard!! I am definitely on you with all these points! 
What I am saying is that there are a lot of home made mask being sold online which gives people a false sense of security that it will definitely protect them. Well I do agree that they will protect them to some extent but is that enough? So because I have seen this phenomenon, I am lucky to have found a supplier who has access to anti microbial fabric. Which inhibits and destroys virus to a better extent (Not fully of course! These have been used in their local Hospitals. If you ask me can they prevent the virus 100%. Of course not. But are they better than cloth mask? I will like to believe so given it is used in hospitals. So if parents can afford, I will like to encourage them to get these for their kids instead of those normal cloth masks.
